cs351.core

Class Vector3

  • java.lang.Object
    • cs351.core.Vector3

  • public final class Vector3
extends java.lang.Object
    Java's Point classes don't let you set a new value for the individual components, forcing you to create a new object even to make the smallest change. This class gets around this limitation. Note that this is bare-bones (cross product, dot product, etc. are left out) because of the very limited way we use this class.
    Author:
    Justin Hall
